
HOW TO COMPILE AND RUN GT_T

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

To compile:
1. mkdir compiled
2. modify the Makefile according your system (compiler and library paths)
3. make
If everything works fine, you will have the executable gt_t.x

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

To run a simulation:
1. ulimit -s unlimited (this is to unlimit the stack memory)
2. set the enviromental variable KMP_STACKSIZE to a large value (for instance export KMP_STACKSIZE=32G)
3. modify the input_file in order to describe your system (see examples).
4. run "nohup gt_t.x < input_file &"  

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 
